  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A group of midwives and obstetric nurses have been trained to use circumferential abdominal
      pelvic pressure (CAPP) to treat postpartum hemorrhage. As part of the training follow up any
      use of a CAPP device will be monitored to identify complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Providers will be surveyed twice at 4 and 8 months using open ended methods.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
